-- 
Bundesbank May Appoint First Female Board Member, Welt Reports

-- B y   B r i a n   P a r k i n
-- 
2011-02-16T08:09:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-16/bundesbank-may-appoint-first-female-board-member-welt-reports.html
The Bundesbank’s board may get its
first female member with the possible appointment of BaFin
executive director for banking supervision, Sabine Lautenschlaeger,  Die Welt  reported, citing no one.  Bonn-based Lautenschlaeger may be appointed in a reshuffle
of top posts at the central bank that may include Jens Weidmann,
Chancellor  Angela Merkel ’s top economic adviser, being appointed
president, the newspaper said.  BaFin is the federal government’s bank and financial
services regulator.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Parkin in Berlin at 
 bparkin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
James Hertling at   jhertling@bloomberg.net  